FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1783925469
OL,3,CBody of man recovered from reservoir
OL,5,FIt is understood the man, who was in
OL,6,Fhis 40s, entered the reservoir but
OL,7,Ffailed to resurface. Bystanders and
OL,8,Fmembers of the public attempted to
OL,9,Fsave him before emergency crews
OL,10,Farrived at the scene.
OL,12,FA large emergency response was
OL,13,Fdeployed at around 8.30pm, with crews
OL,14,Ffrom Greater Manchester Fire and
OL,15,FRescue Service, GMP, and the North
OL,16,FWest Ambulance Service seen searching
OL,17,Fthe water before a body was found.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1783925469
OL,3,CBody of man recovered from reservoir
OL,5,FSuperintendent Dave Henthorne from
OL,6,FGMP's Stockport district said:
OL,7,F"Despite the best efforts of all
OL,8,Femergency services at the scene, the
OL,9,Fbody of a 49-year-old man was
OL,10,Frecovered after an extensive search.
OL,12,F"Our thoughts are first and foremost
OL,13,Fwith his family and loved ones at this
OL,14,Ftragic time."
OL,16,FAt least 10 people have died in open
OL,17,Fwater in the North West of England in
OL,18,F2026.
OL,26,@oD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1783925469
OL,3,CBody of man recovered from reservoir
OL,5,FFollowing the death in Stockport,
OL,6,Femergency services have renewed their
OL,7,Furgent warnings about the dangers of
OL,8,Fopen water, urging the public to stay
OL,9,Fout of reservoirs, rivers, and lakes
OL,10,Fduring the current heatwave.
OL,12,FSupt Int Henthorne added: "We are
OL,13,Fcurrently looking into the full
OL,14,Fcircumstances of the incident however
OL,15,Fwe'd like to remind people of the
OL,16,Fserious risks associated with open
OL,17,Fwater.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1783925469
OL,3,CBody of man recovered from reservoir
OL,5,F"It has been extremely warm recently
OL,6,Fwhich is set to continue into the
OL,7,Fweekend; however, we would urge
OL,8,Feveryone to stay safe and avoid
OL,9,Fentering reservoirs, rivers, canals or
OL,10,Fponds.
OL,12,F"Please take care of yourselves and
OL,13,Feach other and enjoy the warm weather
OL,14,Fsafely."
OL,16,FAn amber heat-health alert is in place
OL,17,Ffor most of England until 9pm on
OL,18,FSunday, 12 July, with some areas
OL,19,Fexpected to get temperatures of up to
OL,20,F33 degrees.
OL,26,@tD@AOUvD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
